<HEADLINE>
FT  12 FEB 94 / Senator acquitted
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUREK MARTIN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Senator Kay Bailey Hutchison of Texas was yesterday acquitted on charges of
misusing a previous state office after the prosecution asked that the
charges against her be dropped, writes Jurek Martin in Washington.
The case almost certainly means that Ms Hutchison, a Republican elected last
year to fill out the unexpired term of Mr Lloyd Bentsen, now treasury
secretary, will be easily returned in November to a full six years in the
Senate. She was only the 10th sitting senator in US history to face criminal
prosecution.
The state withdrew its case after the judge had refused to rule on the
admissibility of certain evidence concerning the charges that Ms Hutchison
had misued her previous office as Texas treasurer for personal and campaign
purposes.
