FT  11 FEB 94 / International Company News: Cost savings lift Petrobras
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK MCCURRY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAO PAULO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Petrobras, Brazil's government-controlled oil company, reported net profits
of Dollars 673m for 1993 compared with Dollars 53m for 1992. The company
said the improvement was due to increased productivity and cost savings.
Mr Marcos Menezes, head of Petrobras's accounting division, said the company
increased production from an average 653,000 barrels per day in 1992 to
671,000 last year. He added that Petrobras saved Dollars 600m in operational
costs in 1993, Dollars 400m of which was due to lower financial costs after
a switch from expensive long-term financing in the local market and
comparatively low interest rates in international markets.
Net turnover for the period was Dollars 13.79bn.
