<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Coal shares suspended at 76p
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Coal Investments, formerly Geevor, were suspended at 76p last
night 'in view of the continuing press comment' about 'the future of certain
closed collieries previously operated by British Coal Corporation'.
CI has exercised its option to acquire from Edwards Energy, a private
company controlled by Mr Michael Edwards, CI chairman. British Coal has said
that Edwards Energy is the preferred bidder for Coventry, Trentham and
Markham Main collieries.
The shares will remain suspended until CI announces the terms of the
transactions and the associated fundraising.
</TEXT>
