<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Perhaps the UN ought to have designated a Day Of The Family rather than a
Year: those not sick to death of the family before the year began are pretty
sure to be by the time television has finished with it. Today C4 begins
Faces Of The Family, a series in which Mavis Nicholson interviews various
members of one extended family. She begins with Pauline Crabbe, a black
social worker who is on her third husband. Clearly an expert (8.00).
With television nothing succeeds like excess. Last Friday Alexei Sayle was
the main guest on The Unpleasant World Of Penn And Teller, a conjuring show
(10.30 C4). Yesterday BBC2 gave us 'The All New Alexei Sayle Show'. At 8.50
this evening BBC1 brings us Drive with Alexei Sayle telling us how to make
the roads safer. Then, at 9.30, BBC2 gets Alexei Sayle to launch the BBC
Design Awards 1994. Why not just give him John Birt's job and have done with
it.
BBC2 ends its rerun of Series 1 of Red Dwarf at 9.00. Then, at 10.00 BBC2
repeats an unforgettable episode of Blackadder II.
</TEXT>
