<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Passport photos
'decriminalised'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
People who think their passport photo makes them look like a criminal rather
than a tourist will be pleased to know that Societe Francaise de
Technologies (Soft), of Pleuhiden, France, has come up with a high-tech
photo booth which claims to produce a far more flattering photo.
To begin with the client chooses his or her 'best side' by looking at
possible shots on television mini-screens. The absence of a flash means the
model will not look startled. And because the photo is produced by
chemical-free thermal imaging the photos emerge from the machine dry, and so
do not stick together. Soft: France, 96 83 29 49.
</TEXT>
