   LE GUILVINEC
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
French fishermen voted overwhelmingly yesterday to extend their 12-day-old
strike over cheap fish imports, Reuter reports from Le Guilvinec.
Bowing to the protests, the government has tightened border controls on fish
imports and granted fishermen FFr450m (Pounds 51m) aid.
