<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 94 / World News in Brief: Former terrorist chief McGlinchey
killed in ambush
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dominic McGlinchey, 40, the former terrorist chief whose brutality earned
him the nickname Mad Dog, was shot dead by three gunmen in an ambush at
Drogheda, County Louth, in the Irish republic last night. Mr McGlinchey had
been leader of the outlawed Irish National Liberation Army, a breakaway
faction from the IRA, and boasted of taking part in 30 murders. He was
released from the republic's Portlaoise jail last year after serving seven
years of a 10-year sentence for firearms offences. Pressure on Sinn Fein
stepped up, Page 10
</TEXT>
