FT  10 FEB 94 / EU call for Chinese ban
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STRASBOURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Union should ban the sale of goods produced by forced labour in
China until Beijing ends the practice and improves human rights, the
European parliament said yesterday, Reuter reports from Strasbourg.
Calling for the inclusion of a human rights clause in EU trade agreements
with third countries, the parliament said it would not approve any new
co-operation agreement with China until there were 'significant changes'
there.
